==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: amnesty
<hw>am"nes*ty</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m"n⟦ecr⟧s*t⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>amnestia</ets>, Gr. <grk>'amnhsti`a</grk>, a forgetting,
fr. <grk>'a`mnhstos</grk> forgotten, forgetful; <grk>'a</grk> priv. +
<grk>mna^sqai</grk> to remember: cf. F. <ets>amnistie</ets>, earlier
<ets>amnestie</ets>. See <er>Mean</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Forgetfulness; cessation of remembrance of wrong;
oblivion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An act of the sovereign power granting oblivion, or
a general pardon, for a past offense, as to subjects concerned in an
insurrection.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amnesty</ent>⟦br⟧

